Yeah, I hate Trynd too, but all you have to do is pick one of those "FU-team-singleplayer-mode-for-this-game" champions, which include, but are not reduced to: {{champion:24}} {{champion:75}} {{champion:2}} {{champion:17}}

Even if you lose lane against him, these guys will stay on top lane as well, and since you started the game with the mentality of not leaving it anytime soon, being forced to stay there won't be much of a problem.

Or, if instead you care about your team (unlike the Tryn player), you can pick one of those "I'll crush your dreams of scoring a kill 1v1 once I finish my first defensive item" champions like {{champion:86}} {{champion:54}} {{champion:57}} {{champion:78}} {{champion:33}}

